title: Baltimore Bridge Collapse: Former Captain Breaks Down What We Know | WSJ
description:
The Francis Scott Key Bridge in Baltimore collapsed into the Patapsco River after being hit by a large containership. The Singaporean cargo ship, charted by shipping giant A.P. Moller-Maersk, smashed into a support beam, causing the entire structure to topple. 

WSJ explains how the incident unfolded and the impact it could have on one of America's busiest ports.
